[Name] XMonad
[Summary] a tiling window manager
[License] BSD3
[Description] xmonad is a tiling window manager for X. Windows are arranged automatically to tile the screen without gaps or overlap, maximising screen use. All features of the window manager are accessible from the keyboard: a mouse is strictly optional. xmonad is written and extensible in Haskell. 
[Homepage] http://xmonad.org/
